  "input": "HDJ RE-hospitalization report\nThe child Amroun Abdel Aziz, aged 09 from Chlef and residing in Oran, followed in our department since 11/01/2021 for a primary immunodeficiency type \"Wiskott Aldrich syndrome\", complicated by dilation of the cylindrical DDB bronchi and chronic respiratory failure stage 1. Admitted on 03/11/2025 for his treatment 49 immunoglobulins\nHistory of illness:\nMain diagnosis: Wiskott Aldrich type DIP\nDate of diagnosis: 12/11/2020\nAge of diagnosis: 04 years and 9 months\nAssociated diagnoses: Dilation of the cylindrical bronchi\nChronic respiratory failure stage 1\nDiagnostic elements:\nAnamnestics\n-Male gender\n-Repeated respiratory infections\n-Several outbreaks of eczema. Clinic\n-Anemic syndrome consisting of: mucocutaneous pallor. -Skin hemorrhagic syndrome such as petechiae spread to the face and trunk. -Eczema lesions on the face and lower limbs. Para-clinical:\n-Bi cytopenia; anemia, thrombocytopenia\n- Assessment of primary immunodeficiency: 12/29/2020, Profound reduction in the expression of the WASp protein results in favor of DIP Wiskott Aldrich syndrome\nImmunoglobulin treatment at a rate of 0.8mg1/kg/4h at the SAP each month. Last dose received: 02/09/2026 (0.8g/kg)\nLast update made in May 2025\nHISTORY OF HOSPITALIZATIONS\nANAMNESIS 03/11/2025\nEvents since the last visit: 10/13/2026\nConsultation: no\nOn the respiratory level: wet cough, clear sputum,\nSigns of respiratory failure: Clubbing\nNutritionally: good food intake\nOn the digestive level: Preserved transit\nOn the ENT level: Nothing to report\nActivity: dyspnea\nSchooling: 3rd year of primary school\nProcessing in progress:\nAzithromycin 1 day out of 02\nBactrim 25mg/kg/d\nItraconazole 05mg/kg/day: 02 times/day\nPulmicort 1mg: 02 times/day\nNebulization with hypertonic salt serum\nRespiratory physiotherapy done by the mother\nWell-kept notebooks\nAssessments made:\nIgG level: 9.21 g/l (06/07/2025)\nCLINICAL EXAMINATION UPON ADMISSION: Date: 03/11/2025\n-Anthropometric measurements:\nWeight: 30kg [-0.018 DS] Height: 130 cm [-0.97DS] BMI: 17.7 kg/m2 Eutrophic child\n-General condition preserved, conscious, T: 37.2\n-Skin examination: no cutaneous and mucosal hemorrhagic syndrome, dry skin, multiple scars on the lower limbs\n-Pleuropulmonary examination: FR: 38c/min SPo2: 96% Under 2 liters of O2, slight signs of struggle. Thoracic keel deformity, clubbing\n. Auscultation of polymorphic rales\n-Cardiovascular examination: HR: 98 bpm, Auscultation: no murmur/no added noises\n-Examination of the abdomen: flexible transit preserved, no organomegaly\n-ENT examination: Presence of dental caries, absence of hemorrhagic bubbles\n-Examination of other devices without anomalies\nParaclinical assessment at admission: 03/11/2025:\nFNS: WBC: 5400 elements/ul (PNN: 4300 Lymph: 1100) Hb: 10.3 g/dl Platelet: 37,000 elements/ul\nCRP: 16mg TQ: 15.6 Sec TP: 69.6% TCK: 30 Sec\nSupport:\n-Hospitalization\n- Conditioning, peripheral venous route\n-Replacement immunotherapy: IV infusion at 0.8g/kg or 25g, to be administered over 4 hours (Intratect)\n-Monitoring\nThe immunoglobulin treatment passed without incident\nSame day release\nContinue the same treatment: bactrim antibiotic prophylaxis and itraconazole antifungal\nZithromax, Pulmicort\nPhysiotherapy and saline nebulizations\nHygiene-dietary advice and notebook keeping\nControl appointment: 11/23/2025 for immunoglobulin treatment\nTo collect / To do:\nNext immunoglobulin treatment appointment is scheduled for 04/14/2026\nPlan an ECBC to recover before the next treatment\nPlan a chest CT,\nSchedule an abdominopelvic ultrasound\nSchedule an echocardiogram\nStomato advice (dental caries)\nRetrieve the health record\nSibling screening\nDepartment resident: Dr Djoudi Department assistant: Dr Khelil",
  "target": "Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome",
